{
  "text": "For the SPM samples, the analysis of GDGTs incore and intact polar lipid fractions was carried out as described by [CITATION_1] . For the marine sediments, the polar DCM:MeOH fractions were analyzed for core lipid GDGTs as described by [CITATION_2] . The fractions were dried down under N 2 , redissolved by sonication (5 min) in nhexane:propan-2-ol (99:1, v:v) to a concentration of ca. 2 mg/ml and filtered through 0.45 \u00b5m PTFE filters. The samples were analyzed using HPLC-APCI-MS according to the procedure described by [CITATION_3] , with minor modifications. GDGTs were detected using selective ion monitoring of (M+H) + ions (dwell time 237 ms) and quantification was achieved by integrating peak areas and using the C 46 GDGT internal standard according to [CITATION_4] . Note that the two different extraction methods used for quantification of GDGTs of core lipids should provide comparable results (cf. [CITATION_5] .",
  "correct_citation": {
